race.comment: RIDEAU (1) led throughout last start to score effortlessly over this track and trip. Unbeaten over this distance from three attempts and keeps gun hoop in Wiggins aboard. The one to beat. RICH AGAIN (6) only boasts the two career wins but is a consistent gelding, placing on 11 occasions. The engagement of Ashley Butler is a positive move. Best figures measure right up and he's sure to run well again. DEALING'S DONE (4) is a locally trained gelding who has been freshened since being narrowly beaten last time at Townsville in a blanket finish. Drops back to a winning trip and should be very competitive. PERIGEAN (5) got things back on track last start when sticking on gamely into the placings after leading them up. Open to further improvement and can give this a shake. SPIN DOCTOR (7) won at Twin Hills two starts ago but was below his best last time at Bowen. Better over the shorter trip. Keeping safe.
